body:
**Description of the problem**

<!-- Please be as detailed as you can when describing an issue. The more information we have, the easier it will be for us to track this down. -->

There seems to be a dependency resolver/timeout problem with the `conda install` step in PyGMT's `ci_tests.yaml`', specifically for the `ubuntu-latest - Python 3.9 / NumPy 1.20` build. This appears to have happened after GDAL was upgraded from 3.2 to 3.3 at https://github.com/conda-forge/gmt-feedstock/pull/150.

**Full code that generated the error**

See https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/pygmt/runs/2626832477 and https://github.com/GenericMappingTools/pygmt/runs/2626832477?check_suite_focus=true

**Full error message**

<details>

```
UnsatisfiableError: The following specifications were found
to be incompatible with the existing python installation in your environment:

Specifications:

  - codecov -> python[version='2.7.*|3.5.*|3.6.*']
  - glib -> python[version='2.7.*|3.6.*|3.7.*|3.8.*']
  - libgdal -> python[version='2.7.*|3.5.*|3.6.*|>=2.7,<2.8.0a0|>=3.5,<3.6.0a0|>=3.6,<3.7.0a0|3.4.*']
  - postgresql -> python[version='2.7.*|3.5.*|3.6.*|>=2.7,<2.8.0a0|>=3.5,<3.6.0a0|>=3.6,<3.7.0a0|3.4.*']
  - pytest-mpl -> python[version='2.7.*|3.4.*|3.5.*|3.6.*']

Your python: python=3.9

If python is on the left-most side of the chain, that's the version you've asked for.
When python appears to the right, that indicates that the thing on the left is somehow
not available for the python version you are constrained to. Note that conda will not
change your python version to a different minor version unless you explicitly specify
that.
```
